CRTP = Curiously Recurring Template Pattern


------------------------------------------------
template<typename Derived>
class Base 
{
    // use static_cast to call derived
};

class Derived : public Base<Derived> 
{
    //
};
-------------------------------------------------
Why Use CRTP?
    Compile-time polymorphism Instead of virtual functions (runtime polymorphism)

    No vtable
    No virtual call overhead
    Better inlining
    Faster (important in trading systems)
------------------------------------------------------
Real Trading Example Use

    template<typename Strategy>
    class Engine 
    {
    public:
        void run() 
        {
            static_cast<Strategy*>(this)->onTick();
        }
    };

    Each strategy implements onTick().
    No virtual call in hot path.
---------------------------------------------------------